&lt;p&gt;commit c4bf767afcc28f96fbfed35cc97ce58b5de009fa&lt;br/&gt;
Author: Till Rohrmann &amp;lt;trohrmann@apache.org&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Date:   2017-09-20T15:39:35Z&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-7655&quot; title=&quot;Revisit default non-leader id for FencedRpcEndpoints&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-7655&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-7655&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;flip6&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Set fencing token to null if not leader&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    This commit changes the fencing behaviour such that a component which is not the&lt;br/&gt;
    leader will set its fencing token to null. This distinction allows to throw different&lt;br/&gt;
    exceptions depending on whether it is a token mismatch or whether the receiver has&lt;br/&gt;
    no fencing token set (== not being the leader).&lt;/p&gt;

